The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 October is 5,043 (583.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 October, there were 528 new confirmed cases (61.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 October, there were 385 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 37% ( 143 extra cases).
